{
  "stem": "15197.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Why do you think we don't pay more attention to these mothers?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We don't-- why I think-- our time is so different from the time that I lived in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Time is now most is taken with action.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's say resistance is understood if you have a gun, if you stand up with a knife, if you do something.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The resistance in different forms which was expressed in the time of the occupation in the ghetto was very often a different way of resistance which has to be understood if you go back to these particular years.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not the gun and the revolt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was the inner strength, it was the tradition, the morality, the ethic which our mothers lived and our generations before us lived, and it was expressed in simple, little things, in 1,000 instances of resistance about we take it for granted.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We don't mention this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But at that time, it was more than little things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was strength, which has to be understood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say that later on when I got involved more in the illegal work and we start thinking and when deportation were held, about deportation in other ghettos, in other towns, and most of the people who were in the youth underground, the organized, not in the hundreds of hundreds, but a very small group.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were, in a way, the foundation of the later organized, armed resistance which took place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when I look back, I think that the armed resistance was possible because it was an ethical, moral resistance going on in the ghetto before deportation.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is a chain.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It didn't come suddenly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The young people came from the houses of the parents who were transported to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
